g.text: LeetCode is a platform that helps software engineers prepare for coding interviews. It offers a collection of practice coding problems
for users to solve and get feedback on their solutions. They also host competitions where users can compete to solve
as many questions as possible in a set amount of time.
1. Users should be able to view a given problem and code a solution in multiple languages
2. Users should be able to submit their solution and get instant feedback
3. Users should be able to compete in competitions and view a live leaderboard to see who's winning
- 300k daily active users, max 100k per competition
- scalability to be able to handle larger number of concurrent competition users (100k)
- Near realtime leaderboard for competition < 200ms latency
- setup within own vpc to prevent network traffic out
- seccomp to prevent access to system calls
